Be sure to tune in to the Laconia press conference this morning at 10AM.

A City of Laconia press conference regarding the COVID-19 virus will be held on Wednesday, August 12, 2020 at 10:00 am. The press conference will be live streamed by Lakes Region Public Access Television and will be a joint conference between the City of Laconia departments and the Laconia School District.

To watch the press conference live, please use the following link: https://livestream.com/lrpatv/laconia



You can also view the press conference at a later time using the link above, or on Channels 24 or 25 if you are a Laconia Atlantic Broadband subscriber.

Please call the City Manager's office at 527-1270 with questions.

Language, Choice and Balance: A conversation with Mike Anderson.

In this podcast, author and consultant, Mike Anderson and Laconia Superintendent of Schools Steve Tucker, discuss the challenges of self-directed learning during the COVID-19 crisis. How do we support true self-direction (not simple compliance) in students as they work from home? What are some practical strategies teachers can try? They also discuss how to support self-directed learning in ways that are manageable and not overwhelming for teachers.

Laconia High School
May 4 at 10:29 AM ·

LHS Class of 2020:

if you get a chance, take a drive by the high school there is a tribute to you from staff and parents on the front lawn! We have a personalized sign for each of you next to a larger one commemorating your class! Please don't take it yet, we plan on getting them to you by early next week to display at your residences.

I would like to leave them up as group for a couple of days as a tribute to you and allow for people to take photographs if they want. Cars are already driving by honking their horns as a tribute. So, please don't take your sign yet. Don't worry about them being stolen the front of the high school is under video surveillance 24/7. We are still working on the logistics to get the signs to you. There will be an email to follow with directions on how we are going to do that.

Take care,

Mr. Fredericksen

If you your child is having a problem with his/her school issued device:

2) If your device needs to be repaired, you will be scheduled to come to Laconia High School.

Please keep in mind that all systems on the internet are being pushed to their maximum capacity which may cause slow downs on the user end.

shared_text:
Belknap Mill
March 17 at 10:49 AM ·

Hey Neighbors!

Over the next few weeks, many of us will be increasing our time spent at home. It can be hard to find things to do all day (especially with children) and not lose your mind. So I was thinking about a way for our community to still get outside and do something fun, without touching or coughing near others.

I thought it’d be fun to have a neighborhood wide rainbow 🌈 hunt!

All you have to do is put a rainbow in your window between now and this Friday. That’s it! Color it, paint it, cut it out, print it from the printer, whatever.

Then we can get outside, walk around and see how many rainbows we can find!

It’s easy. No human contact. Get fresh air. Make a rainbow and then hunt for others.

What do you think? A fun art project that becomes a great outdoor activity!

*sharing someone else’s wonderful idea

Laconia School District Office of School Wellness
December 17, 2019 at 12:21 PM ·

We are proud to announce that we were able to collect 1,749 cans in total from all the schools in the district for our Fall Food Drive!

We were more than happy to partner with St. Vincent De Paul for this drive. We received a letter from them informing us that with our donations and their amazing staff, we were able to satisfy 717 requests for Thanksgiving baskets, this year.

Thank you to all who donated!

post_text:
Attention PSS Families:

Due to the inclement weather, we will be having the PSS Halloween Parade ONSITE today.

The Parade will start at 2:00. We will exit the gym and go around the walking path and re-enter PSS through the 5th grade door. If it is raining hard, we will have to cancel the parade all together.

Due to safety concerns, we are asking families to observe the parade outside, as we have always done in the past. Parking will be limited.

If you are helping a classroom teacher, you must sign in.

Thanks for your understanding and support.

~PSS Staff
